  "summary": "Possible name-confusion package with empty implementation",
  "details": "The package name 'requests-toolbelt-plus' closely resembles the widely-used 'requests-toolbelt' package, but the distribution contains no functional implementation. setup.py contains only setuptools boilerplate (find_packages() with install_requires=['requests']), and requests_toolbelt_plus/__init__.py is a 0-byte file. No code executes at install or import time, and there is no payload (no exfiltration, no remote fetch, no credential access). This release does not actively harm installers, but the name-confusion shape against a popular target with an empty body is a classic squat-placeholder pattern that future versions could weaponize. Routing for human review to confirm intent.",
